The paper deals with graph theory and specifically the topological containment problem, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the study of graph minors, which is a topic in graph theory and graph algorithms (cs.GT). The proof techniques used in the paper involve connectivity and subdivisions, which are topics in graph theory and discrete structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on finding a good characterisation of graphs that do not topologically contain a specific pattern graph suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of structural informatics (cs.SI).
